---
date: 2026-05-28
topic: trailblazers
level: medium
---

The Golden Gate Bridge opened to traffic today in 1937. The experts said you couldn't span that strait — too deep, too foggy, too much current. They ran the numbers, ignored the consensus, and built it anyway. Eighty-nine years later it's still standing. Grateful for the engineers who treat "impossible" as a starting estimate.
